<subSubSection id="4ACE80BDA81ED70CB7B7FA273F9575E7" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="026BD336A81ED70CB7B7FA27390076F4" blockId="4.[207,1190,1432,1697]" box="[207,563,1432,1459]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
<heading id="5923645AA81ED70CB7B7FA27390076F4" box="[207,563,1432,1459]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81ED70CB7B7FA27390076F4" authority="(Rossi, 1790)" baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[207,563,1432,1459]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avidus">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81ED70CB7B7FA27390076F4" bold="true" box="[207,563,1432,1459]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81ED70CB7B7FA273AA376F5" bold="true" box="[207,400,1432,1459]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Merodon avidus</emphasis>
(Rossi, 1790)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="026BD336A81ED70CB7B7FA043F9575E7" blockId="4.[207,1190,1432,1697]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
Il existe deux taxons de cette espèce décris par 
<bibRefCitation id="6645AEC7A81ED70CB473FA043F267693" author="Milankov V. &amp; Vujic A. &amp; Ludoski J." box="[779,1045,1467,1493]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" pagination="15 - 24" refId="ref4623" refString="Milankov V., Vujic A. &amp; Ludoski J. 2001. Genetic divergence among cryptic taxa of Merodon avidus (Rossi, 1790) (Diptera: Syrphidae). International Journal of Dipterological Research 12: 15 - 24." type="journal article" year="2001">Milankov et al. (2001)</bibRefCitation>
: Taxon A et Taxon B. La distribution géographique du Taxon A semble confinée au pourtour nord de la Méditerranée. Le Taxon B est largement distribué de l’Afrique du Nord au sud de la 
<collectingCountry id="7AC393A6A81ED70CB793F99E3A07757D" box="[235,308,1569,1595]" name="Sweden" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Suède</collectingCountry>
. Selon toute probabilité nous avons donc affaire ici au Taxon B. Cette espèce commune en 
<collectingCountry id="7AC393A6A81ED70CB615F9FC3A84751B" box="[365,439,1603,1629]" name="Switzerland" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Suisse</collectingCountry>
vit autant dans des habitats forestiers, allant des hêtraies montagnardes humides à épicéas aux chênaies thermophiles de plaine, que dans des milieux ouverts tels que les prairies sèches de basse altitude. Les larves phytophages semblent
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4ACE80BDA81ED70DB7B7F9163997724A" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" type="description">
<paragraph id="026BD336A81ED70CB7B7F9163F957585" blockId="4.[207,1190,1705,1731]" box="[207,1190,1705,1731]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">s’adapter à de nombreuses plantes hôtes en fonction du biotope. Cependant, il est</paragraph>
<paragraph id="026BD336A81FD70DB7B0FFC239AF73C9" blockId="5.[200,668,124,145]" box="[200,668,124,145]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">GAËL PÉTREMAND &amp; MARTIN C. D. SPEIGHT</paragraph>
<paragraph id="026BD336A81FD70DB7B0FF6F399773AC" blockId="5.[200,676,208,404]" box="[200,676,208,235]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">intéressant de noter l’observation faite</paragraph>
<paragraph id="026BD336A81FD70DB7B0FF4D3997724A" blockId="5.[200,676,208,404]" box="[200,676,242,269]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">d’une femelle pondant sur les feuilles d’un</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4ACE80BDA81FD70DB7B0FEAA39907216" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="026BD336A81FD70DB7B0FEAA39977268" blockId="5.[200,676,208,404]" box="[200,676,276,302]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81FD70DB7B0FEAA39937268" authority="(Reemer &amp; Goudsmits 2004)" baseAuthorityName="Reemer &amp; Goudsmits" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[200,672,276,302]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81FD70DB7B0FEAA3A147268" box="[200,295,277,302]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Muscari</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="6645AEC7A81FD70DB646FEAB39AA7268" author="Reemer M. &amp; Goudsmits K." box="[318,665,276,302]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" pagination="217 - 218" refId="ref4722" refString="Reemer M. &amp; Goudsmits K. 2004. Oviposition observed in Chrysotoxum cautum, C. vernale and Merodon avidus (Diptera, Syrphidae). Volucella 7: 217 - 218." type="journal article" year="2004">Reemer &amp; Goudsmits 2004</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="026BD336A81FD70DB7B0FE8839907216" blockId="5.[200,676,208,404]" box="[200,675,310,337]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
Deux espèces de 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81FD70DB6EEFE883AC47216" baseAuthorityName="Reemer &amp; Goudsmits" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[406,503,311,336]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81FD70DB6EEFE883AC47216" box="[406,503,311,336]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Muscari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sont présentes
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4ACE80BDA81FD70DB7B0FEE7396172D2" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph id="026BD336A81FD70DB7B0FEE739977235" blockId="5.[200,676,208,404]" box="[200,676,344,371]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">dans les vignobles genevois et sont, de ce</paragraph>
<paragraph id="026BD336A81FD70DB7B0FEC5396172D2" blockId="5.[200,676,208,404]" box="[200,594,378,404]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">fait, des plantes hôtes potentielles.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
